First Lady Michelle Obama has announced new commitments to the U.S. government's Let Girls Learn initiative. The initiative aims to provide education to the more than 62 million girls around the world who are out of school. Various organizations have made commitments to support adolescent girls' education, including The UPS Foundation, Lands' End, Xerox Foundation, ALEX AND ANI, Barneys New York, Edelman, IBM, Heidrick & Struggles, JPMorgan Chase, Girls Inc., Girl Scouts of the USA, Sesame Workshop, and the U.S. government. These commitments range from financial contributions to launching programs and campaigns to raise awareness and provide resources for girls' education. The U.S. government will also be launching a $25 million Let Girls Learn Challenge Fund to find solutions to the global girls' education crisis.